comments[6]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T19:06:35.921Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: no active command-path item exposes background lifecycle commands for linked tests; this task scopes command wiring only."
  "2026-04-04T20:22:20.333Z",codex-agent,Implemented --background wiring for pm test/test-all and new test-runs list/status/logs/stop/resume command surface; linked test regression suite passed (55 tests).
  "2026-04-06T19:39:57.090Z",codex-agent,Duplicate-check evidence refreshed via pm context/list/search sweep. Reusing this task for pm test-runs root command non-silent behavior (default list/help) plus runtime regression coverage; no new duplicate task created.
  "2026-04-06T19:48:48.844Z",codex-agent,"Progress: wired root test-runs command to default to runTestRunsList when no subcommand is provided, making pm test-runs non-silent and deterministic. Added integration regression coverage in tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts (bare test-runs returns list payload) and verified via node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts."
  "2026-04-07T18:14:23.933Z",codex-agent,"2026-04-07 scope extension: harden background run requested_by attribution fallback chain to PM_AUTHOR -> USER -> whoami -> unknown and keep metadata deterministic across environments."
  "2026-04-07T18:57:56.505Z",codex-agent,Hardened background run requested_by attribution fallback chain to explicit author -> PM_AUTHOR -> settings author_default -> USER/LOGNAME/USERNAME -> whoami -> unknown. Added focused unit coverage to prevent regressions in shared environments.
